cs.MA, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.NE, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
1. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) - The paper deals with a network of mobile robots and proposes a control scheme for achieving a desired set of adjacency eigenvalues. This falls under the domain of multi-agent systems.
2. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper deals with a network of mobile robots and proposes a control scheme for achieving a desired set of adjacency eigenvalues. This falls under the domain of robotics.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a control scheme for modifying the structure of a network of mobile robots. This falls under the domain of systems and control.
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper employs a gradient descent closed-loop system for minimizing artificial potentials. This falls under the domain of neural and evolutionary computing.
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper deals with the eigenvalue spectrum of the adjacency matrix of a network and proposes a novel abstraction of the eigenvalue spectrum by means of the adjacency matrix spectral moments. This falls under the domain of data structures and algorithms.
